cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses progress made on the Omniglot dataset, which is commonly used in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses computational models and approaches to address the challenges presented by the dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses image classification and recognition, which are common topics in cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions the need for a single model to perform multiple tasks, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
